            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@tpope (maintainer of the [vim-markdown](https://github.com/tpope/vim-markdown) plugin) Thanks much for joining the discussion and giving your insights. \n\nIn case `smartindent` may not be a smart thing to use with markdown syntax :-), would you could support, adding in your syntax plugin\n\n```\nsetlocal nosmartindent\n```\n? \n(In case you agree, I'm glad to open a PR with this minor change.)\n\nA number of syntaxt plugins seem to do the same.\nThis could allow for the user keeping a global `smartindent` option (if for some reason preferred), yet safely editing markdown files.\n",
