            "body": "@zeertzjq Thanks for the highlight. So, I rephrase my question to @tpope :\n\"May it be useful to add a minimal indent definition to [vim-markdown](https://github.com/tpope/vim-markdown) with `setlocal nosmartindent`? Allowing for users to keep their global `smartindent` setting, yet overridden when editing markdown.\"\n(If yes, I'm still good to volunteer :-) )\n\n(I also take the chance to clarify, just to avoid confusion: bringing attention to 11 years old attempt for markdown indent was rather express that the idea seem to have been around before. No attempt to use or integrate outdated code. Of course not even to use such solution if the idea is evaluated as inconvenient.)",
