        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> In case `smartindent` may not be a smart thing to use with markdown syntax :-), would you could support, adding in your syntax plugin\n> \n> ```\n> setlocal nosmartindent\n> ```\n\nI see 748 syntax files in `runtime/syntax/`. *Maybe* 50 of them would work decently with `'smartindent'`. Would you propose adding `setlocal nosmartindent` to the other 698?\n\n> This could allow for the user keeping a global `smartindent` option (if for some reason preferred)\n\nIf a user prefers this then the user is just wrong, sorry. It's not even documented as a \"global or local\" option, it's just \"local to buffer\". Vim does let you shoot yourself in the foot here, but that's hardly the only instance of that.",
